    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@bobylito I fixed the bug, but I still need to dig a little bit to find a way to allow `refine` on first rendering. Because I based the refinement on the `range` and on the first rendering we have a range of [0, 0] (default value). So, the refinement can't be done properly for the `max` value. It will always be upper than the max bound.",
